  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Vaginal bleeding during pregnancy

          -  Open cervical os.

          -  No signs of severe infection, defined as at least one of the following of: 1) foul
             smelling discharge, 2) fever &gt; 38 degrees C , 3) uterine tenderness

          -  No hemodynamic disturbances (pulse &gt;110/min and systolic bp &lt;100)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Suspected to have an ectopic pregnancy

          -  Unable to provide informed consent
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
